\int_0^{2\pi} \sin(x) dx = \int_0^{2\pi} \cos(x) dx = 0
\int_0^{2\pi} \frac{1}{2} (2\sin \theta + \cos \theta) d\theta= 0
\int_0^{2\pi k} \alpha \sin\left(\frac{x}{k}\right)  + \beta \cos\left(\frac{x}{k}\right) dx = 0 \qquad \forall\ \alpha,\beta,k \in \mathbb R
 \int \sin\theta + \frac{\cos\theta}{2} d\theta=\cos\theta-\frac{\sin\theta}{2}
 \int_0^{2\pi}\sin\theta + \frac{\cos\theta}{2} d\theta=1-1-0+0=0
